{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9a234a92-776d-460c-a920-6144392c1076","content":"Here's what needs to change:\n\n**`.csproj`** — Replace the old assembly reference and `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` with the single MSTest v3 meta-package (it bundles the framework, adapter, and test SDK):","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01HGHrrFLjojR5pYE2uusfzD","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Upgrading to MSTest v3"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_017xV2t4APznF3Lf5RuwdWsH","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-8e921ca2bbd840be90edde62493f4557/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Reference Include=\"Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework\" />\n  </ItemGroup>\n\n  <ItemGroup>\n    <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\" Version=\"17.5.0\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.3\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-8e921ca2bbd840be90edde62493f4557/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"54e0ac25-26dc-4b29-9401-c0cfa656c993","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .NET Framework test project that:\n\n1. Targets `net462`\n2. Uses an assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework` (the old MSTest)\n3. Has `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` 17.5.0\n4. Uses `Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting` namespace in the test code\n\nTo upgrade to MSTest v3, I need to:\n\n1. Remove the old assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n\n\n2. Add the `MSTest` meta-package (v3.x) which bundles the test framework and adapter together\n3. Keep or update `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` since the MSTest meta-package handles the core dependencies\n4. The test code itself doesn't need changes—the `using` statements and attributes like `[TestClass]`, `[TestMethod]`, and `[Timeout]` work the same way in v3\n\nThe cleanest approach is to u